Title: Handle filenames with weird characters

The name of files gets used directly in the compilation guard for C output.
This means an input file named "args-ahoy.smudge" will produce the lines:

<<*>>=
#ifndef __args-ahoy_h__
#define __args-ahoy_h__
@

etc., which doesn't compile.

The best way to fix this is to treat them like RawIds, and cook them.
